(x+1)R(x-1)(x-1)x-(x-1)R(x)x(x+1)=0
x(x-1)(x+1)(R(x-1)-R(x))=0
so R(x-1)=R(x)
Denote a polynomial S(x)=R(x)-R(0), S(x) has infinite roots, so it is the 0 polynomial.
Therefore R(x) is constant for all x, let R(x)=c_1
P(x)=c_1*x*(x+1)+k/2
